{"word":"ἀπονοσφίζω","slug":"ἀπονοσφίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπονοσφίζω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to put asunder, keep aloof from</i>, <el>τινά τινος</el> h. <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to bereave</i> or <i>rob of</i>, <el>ὅπλων τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be robbed of</i>, <el>ἐδωδήν</el> h. <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> loci, <i>to flee from, shun</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}